title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Youth unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points.
Overall Youth unemployment rate has increased over the Year.

Youth unemployment rate is rapidly increasing from 1999 to 2003, roughly constant from 2003 to 2004, slightly increasing from 2004 to 2005, roughly constant from 2005 to 2006, slightly decreasing from 2006 to 2007, roughly constant from 2007 to 2010, rapidly increasing from 2010 to 2012, roughly constant from 2012 to 2013, roughly increasing from 2013 to 2014, and lastly roughly constant from 2014 to 2019.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2006 and 2007.
Max Youth unemployment rate about 34.68 was recorded at Year 2015
Min Youth unemployment rate about 20.13 was recorded at Year 1999
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Youth unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points. The chart has 6 significant trends.
The longest trend is moderately decreasing which exists from 2015 to 2019.
On the other hand, the next significant trend is extremely decreasing which exists from 2008 to 2012.
But, the next significant trend is moderately decreasing which exists from 2012 to 2015.
Contrarily, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2005 to 2008.
Contrarily, the next significant trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2002 to 2005.
